Y -> Current State
H -> Halt state

a b c d -> available state identifiers

1 . + = -> available alphabet identifier (to match unary_adder)
A B C D -> alphabet cursor saver (replace the above chars to save cursor position)

* -> blank character

r l -> identify state action (RIGHT, LEFT)

| -> state transition separator (goes on the left of the transition definition)

X -> machine / tape separator

Steps to do:

find X
replace char by cursor saver

find current state
find cursor
find cursor + current state transition
find write char
find next_state
find action
find cursor
write next char
do action
save cursor
find current state separator
save current state
find halt state separator
if current state == halt state, halt
go back to find current state

example machine: 'YaHd|a1a1rX1'